Git init is the first step in creating a repository.

 Usage

# Change directory to codebase:
$ cd/file/path/to/code

# Make directory a git repository
$ git init

 In Practice

# Change directory to codebase:
$ cd/users/commputer-name/documents/website

# Make directory a git repository:
$ git init
//Initialized empity Git repository in/users/computer-name/documents/website/.git/
